msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamā ākiñcaññāyatanasappāyā paṭipadā akkhāyati. "
msgstr "This is said to be the first way of practice suitable for attaining the dimension of nothingness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc6
msgctxt "mn106:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, and reflects like this: "

msgctxt "mn106:7.2"
msgid "‘suññamidaṃ attena vā attaniyena vā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is empty of a self or what belongs to a self.’ "

msgctxt "mn106:7.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃpaṭipannassa tabbahulavihārino āyatane cittaṃ pasīdati. "
msgstr "Practicing in this way and meditating on it often their mind becomes confident in this dimension. "

msgctxt "mn106:7.4"
msgid "Sampasāde sati etarahi vā ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjati paññāya vā adhimuccati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā. "
msgstr "Being confident, they either attain the dimension of nothingness now, or are freed by wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn106:7.5"
msgid "Ṭhānametaṃ vijjati yaṃ taṃsaṃvattanikaṃ viññāṇaṃ assa ākiñcaññāyatanūpagaṃ. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, it’s possible that the consciousness headed that way will be reborn in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "mn106:7.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyā ākiñcaññāyatanasappāyā paṭipadā akkhāyati. "
msgstr "This is said to be the second way of practice suitable for attaining the dimension of nothingness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli2.264, sc7
msgctxt "mn106:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects: "

#. VAR: kvacani → kvacini (bj-a, s1-3, km)
#. VAR: kiñcanatasmiṃ → kiñcanattasmiṃ (bj) | kiñcanatasmi (?)
msgctxt "mn106:8.2"
msgid "‘nāhaṃ kvacani kassaci kiñcanatasmiṃ, na ca mama kvacani kismiñci kiñcanaṃ natthī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I don’t belong to anyone anywhere! And nothing belongs to me anywhere!’ "

msgctxt "mn106:8.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃpaṭipannassa tabbahulavihārino āyatane cittaṃ pasīdati. "
msgstr "Practicing in this way and meditating on it often their mind becomes confident in this dimension. "

msgctxt "mn106:8.4"
msgid "Sampasāde sati etarahi vā ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjati paññāya vā adhimuccati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā. "
msgstr "Being confident, they either attain the dimension of nothingness now, or are freed by wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn106:8.5"
msgid "Ṭhānametaṃ vijjati yaṃ taṃsaṃvattanikaṃ viññāṇaṃ assa ākiñcaññāyatanūpagaṃ. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, it’s possible that the consciousness headed that way will be reborn in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "mn106:8.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyā ākiñcaññāyatanasappāyā paṭipadā akkhāyati. "
