#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc8
msgctxt "mn106:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects: "

msgctxt "mn106:9.2"
msgid "‘ye ca diṭṭhadhammikā kāmā, ye ca samparāyikā kāmā; "
msgstr "‘Sensual pleasures in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:9.3"
msgid "yā ca diṭṭhadhammikā kāmasaññā, yā ca samparāyikā kāmasaññā; "
msgstr "sensual perceptions in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:9.4"
msgid "ye ca diṭṭhadhammikā rūpā, ye ca samparāyikā rūpā; "
msgstr "visions in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:9.5"
msgid "yā ca diṭṭhadhammikā rūpasaññā, yā ca samparāyikā rūpasaññā; "
msgstr "perceptions of visions in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:9.6"
msgid "yā ca āneñjasaññā, yā ca ākiñcaññāyatanasaññā—"
msgstr "perceptions of the imperturbable, and perceptions of the dimension of nothingness; "

msgctxt "mn106:9.7"
msgid "sabbā saññā. "
msgstr "all are perceptions. "

msgctxt "mn106:9.8"
msgid "Yatthetā aparisesā nirujjhanti etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ—"
msgstr "Where they cease without anything left over, that is peaceful, that is sublime, "

msgctxt "mn106:9.9"
msgid "yadidaṃ nevasaññānāsaññāyatanan’ti. "
msgstr "namely the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’ "

msgctxt "mn106:9.10"
msgid "Tassa evaṃpaṭipannassa tabbahulavihārino āyatane cittaṃ pasīdati. "
msgstr "Practicing in this way and meditating on it often their mind becomes confident in this dimension. "

msgctxt "mn106:9.11"
msgid "Sampasāde sati etarahi vā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjati paññāya vā adhimuccati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā. "
msgstr "Being confident, they either attain the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception now, or are freed by wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn106:9.12"
msgid "Ṭhānametaṃ vijjati yaṃ taṃsaṃvattanikaṃ viññāṇaṃ assa nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagaṃ. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, it’s possible that the consciousness headed that way will be reborn in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "mn106:9.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasappāyā paṭipadā akkhāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "This is said to be the way of practice suitable for attaining the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, pts-vp-pli2.265, sc9
msgctxt "mn106:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "mn106:10.2"
msgid "“idha, bhante, bhikkhu evaṃ paṭipanno hoti: "
msgstr "“Sir, take a mendicant who practices like this: "

msgctxt "mn106:10.3"
msgid "‘no cassa, no ca me siyā; na bhavissati, na me bhavissati; yadatthi yaṃ, bhūtaṃ—taṃ pajahāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘It might not be, and it might not be mine. It will not be, and it will not be mine. I am giving up what exists, what has come to be.’ "

msgctxt "mn106:10.4"
msgid "Evaṃ upekkhaṃ paṭilabhati. "
msgstr "In this way they gain equanimity. "

msgctxt "mn106:10.5"
msgid "Parinibbāyeyya nu kho so, bhante, bhikkhu na vā parinibbāyeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would that mendicant become extinguished or not?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:10.6"
msgid "“Apetthekacco, ānanda, bhikkhu parinibbāyeyya, apetthekacco bhikkhu na parinibbāyeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "“One such mendicant might become extinguished, Ānanda, while another might not.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:10.7"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yenapetthekacco bhikkhu parinibbāyeyya, apetthekacco bhikkhu na parinibbāyeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason for this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:10.8"
msgid "“Idhānanda, bhikkhu evaṃ paṭipanno hoti: "
msgstr "“Ānanda, take a mendicant who practices like this: "

msgctxt "mn106:10.9"
msgid "‘no cassa, no ca me siyā; na bhavissati, na me bhavissati; yadatthi, yaṃ bhūtaṃ—taṃ pajahāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘It might not be, and it might not be mine. It will not be, and it will not be mine. I am giving up what exists, what has come to be.’ "

msgctxt "mn106:10.10"
msgid "Evaṃ upekkhaṃ paṭilabhati. "
msgstr "In this way they gain equanimity. "

msgctxt "mn106:10.11"
msgid "So taṃ upekkhaṃ abhinandati, abhivadati, ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "They approve, welcome, and keep clinging to that equanimity. "

msgctxt "mn106:10.12"
msgid "Tassa taṃ upekkhaṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ hoti viññāṇaṃ tadupādānaṃ. "
msgstr "Their consciousness relies on that and grasps it. "

msgctxt "mn106:10.13"
msgid "Saupādāno, ānanda, bhikkhu na parinibbāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11
msgctxt "mn106:11.1"
msgid "“Kahaṃ pana so, bhante, bhikkhu upādiyamāno upādiyatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what is that mendicant grasping?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:11.2"
msgid "“Nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ, ānandā”ti. "
msgstr "“The dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:11.3"
msgid "“Upādānaseṭṭhaṃ kira so, bhante, bhikkhu upādiyamāno upādiyatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, it seems that mendicant is grasping the best thing to grasp!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:11.4"
msgid "“Upādānaseṭṭhañhi so, ānanda, bhikkhu upādiyamāno upādiyati. "
msgstr "“Indeed, Ānanda. "

msgctxt "mn106:11.5"
msgid "Upādānaseṭṭhañhetaṃ, ānanda, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "For the best thing to grasp is "

msgctxt "mn106:11.6"
msgid "nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ. "
msgstr "the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc10
msgctxt "mn106:12.1"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhu evaṃ paṭipanno hoti: "
msgstr "Take a mendicant who practices like this: "

msgctxt "mn106:12.2"
msgid "‘no cassa, no ca me siyā; na bhavissati, na me bhavissati; yadatthi, yaṃ bhūtaṃ—taṃ pajahāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘It might not be, and it might not be mine. It will not be, and it will not be mine. I am giving up what exists, what has come to be.’ "

msgctxt "mn106:12.3"
msgid "Evaṃ upekkhaṃ paṭilabhati. "
msgstr "In this way they gain equanimity. "

msgctxt "mn106:12.4"
msgid "So taṃ upekkhaṃ nābhinandati, nābhivadati, na ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "They don’t approve, welcome, or keep clinging to that equanimity. "

msgctxt "mn106:12.5"
msgid "Tassa taṃ upekkhaṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ hoti viññāṇaṃ na tadupādānaṃ. "
msgstr "So their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it. "

msgctxt "mn106:12.6"
msgid "Anupādāno, ānanda, bhikkhu parinibbāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, pts-vp-pli2.266, sc11
msgctxt "mn106:13.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn106:13.2"
msgid "Nissāya nissāya kira no, bhante, bhagavatā oghassa nittharaṇā akkhātā. "
msgstr "The Buddha has explained to us how to cross over the flood by relying on one support or the other. "

msgctxt "mn106:13.3"
msgid "Katamo pana, bhante, ariyo vimokkho”ti? "
msgstr "But sir, what is noble liberation?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn106:13.4"
msgid "“Idhānanda, bhikkhu ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "“Ananda, it’s when a mendicant reflects like this: "

msgctxt "mn106:13.5"
msgid "‘ye ca diṭṭhadhammikā kāmā, ye ca samparāyikā kāmā; "
msgstr "‘Sensual pleasures in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:13.6"
msgid "yā ca diṭṭhadhammikā kāmasaññā, yā ca samparāyikā kāmasaññā; "
msgstr "sensual perceptions in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:13.7"
msgid "ye ca diṭṭhadhammikā rūpā, ye ca samparāyikā rūpā; "
msgstr "visions in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:13.8"
msgid "yā ca diṭṭhadhammikā rūpasaññā, yā ca samparāyikā rūpasaññā; "
msgstr "perceptions of visions in this life and in lives to come, "

msgctxt "mn106:13.9"
msgid "yā ca āneñjasaññā, yā ca ākiñcaññāyatanasaññā, yā ca nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññā—"
msgstr "perceptions of the imperturbable, perceptions of the dimension of nothingness, perceptions of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception; "

msgctxt "mn106:13.10"
msgid "esa sakkāyo yāvatā sakkāyo. "
msgstr "that is identity as far as identity extends. "

msgctxt "mn106:13.11"
msgid "Etaṃ amataṃ yadidaṃ anupādā cittassa vimokkho. "
msgstr "This is the deathless, namely the liberation of the mind through not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14
msgctxt "mn106:14.1"
msgid "Iti, kho, ānanda, desitā mayā āneñjasappāyā paṭipadā, desitā ākiñcaññāyatanasappāyā paṭipadā, desitā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasappāyā paṭipadā, desitā nissāya nissāya oghassa nittharaṇā, desito ariyo vimokkho. "
msgstr "So, Ānanda, I have taught the ways of practice suitable for attaining the imperturbable, the dimension of nothingness, and the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. I have taught how to cross the flood by relying on one support or the other, and I have taught noble liberation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15
msgctxt "mn106:15.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, ānanda, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā. "
msgstr "Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples. "

msgctxt "mn106:15.2"
msgid "Etāni, ānanda, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyathānanda, mā pamādattha, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī’”ti. "
msgstr "Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, Ānanda! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn106:15.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn106:15.4"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn106:15.5"
msgid "Āneñjasappāyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

